working directory -------------staging area or index area ---------local repository 
      <-------- git restore     -----------
 <--------------------------git reset -----------------------------------


Revert changes from woring directory 

#git restore file1.txt
or
#git checkout -- file1.txt

Revert changes from Staging area to working area and changes will move to workig directory again 
#git reset file1.txt
or
#git restore --staged file1.rxt

Revert changes from Local Repos  to working area 
#git reset HEAD~1 
or
#git reset --mixed HEAD~1
Revert changes from Local Repos  to Staging  area 
#git reset --soft HEAD~1
Revert changes from Local Repos and discarded 
#git reset --hard HEAD~1

---------------------------------
Git ignore file 
.gitignore

in yuor working directory , i dont want to commit all file , i wnat to skip some file from working directory and commit rest of file 
so we can use .gitignore and move all file name into this file:.gitignore  
when every you commit your file , ignore some file which file names you mention this file .gitignore 





